The paper deals with the design and construction of oversampled filter banks, which are commonly used in signal processing and information theory. The concept of fusion frames, which are sequences of orthogonal projection operators, is introduced and used to provide redundant encodings of signals that are robust against noise and erasures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also emphasizes the use of specific finite impulse response filters, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the construction of implementable filter bank fusion frames, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. However, since the focus of the paper is primarily on signal processing and information theory, we rank cs.IT and cs.SP as the most likely sub-categories.
